===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|竹|聿|t1=bamboo|t2=writing brush|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc}}. {{och-l|*聿}} originally referred to this word; {{och-l|*竹}} was added later to differentiate.

===Etymology===
Possibly from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*b-ris||to draw; picture}} or {{m|sit-pro|*rit||to draw; boundary}} (STEDT). Related to {{och-l|聿}}; more distant cognates from the [[allofam]]ic root {{m|sit-pro|*b-rəy||to draw, mark; boundary}} include {{och-l|理|to cut jade, put in order}}, {{cog|bo|འབྲི||to write}}, {{cog|my|ရေး||to write}}.

{{zh-ref|Benedict (1972)}} surmises that this might ultimately be a loan from Austro-Tai into Sino-Tibetan; compare {{cog|map-pro|*bulut||hairy filaments of certain plants, husk}} (> {{cog|ceb|bulut}}).

